1
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,880
When you're close to someone,

2
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:11,960
maybe you just naturally
want to be even closer.

3
00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:14,599
No wonder when he
wrapped that scarf around me,

4
00:00:14,599 --> 00:00:17,440
I had this sudden urge to kiss him.

5
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:20,038
On the days we can't see each other,

6
00:00:20,038 --> 00:00:22,839
I find myself dying to hear his voice.

7
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,223
[Episode 4: It's Good to Have You Here]

8
00:02:08,136 --> 00:02:10,160
Old Chen, our son is back.

9
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,879
At least say hello.

10
00:02:11,879 --> 00:02:13,479
You're back.

11
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:15,039
How were your final exams?

12
00:02:15,039 --> 00:02:17,759
They were fine.
I think I'll be top of the class.

13
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,039
That's good.

14
00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:21,886
Keep it up.

15
00:02:21,886 --> 00:02:23,680
Still the same bad attitude.

16
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,800
Ke Ke, the flight must have been tiring.

17
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,199
Go to your room and get some rest.

18
00:02:27,199 --> 00:02:30,080
I'll make you something delicious tonight.

19
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,680
Go on.

20
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,000
Here, Lei Lei.

21
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,439
Have some braised pork.

22
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:36,120
It's your favorite.

23
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,870
- Thanks.
- I started cooking early this morning

24
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:39,639
and let it simmer for hours.

25
00:02:39,639 --> 00:02:40,960
It melts in your mouth.

26
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:42,400
- Eat up, eat up.
- Eat.

27
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,587
- Okay, okay.
- While it's hot.

28
00:02:57,735 --> 00:02:59,377
[Yu Lei]

29
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,919
Would that be too sudden?

30
00:03:10,919 --> 00:03:13,319
Ke Ke, we have guests coming over later.

31
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:15,800
Don't forget to shower
and change your clothes.

32
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,841
Mom. Coming!

33
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:25,199
How's this?

34
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:27,519
- Look at this.
- Look.

35
00:03:29,113 --> 00:03:31,353
This is pretty funny.

36
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,680
Yeah, look at that.

37
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,480
Hello?

38
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:43,134
- Mom, it's Aunt Chen on the phone for you.
- Okay.

39
00:03:43,134 --> 00:03:44,718
Go take it.

40
00:03:45,403 --> 00:03:46,920
Son, come here.

41
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,155
I'll take it.

42
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,726
Chen.

43
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,320
It's been a few days.

44
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:57,319
Son, who are you waiting for a call from?

45
00:03:57,319 --> 00:03:58,560
No one.

46
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,639
Just a classmate.

47
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:01,439
- A classmate?
- Yup.

48
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,639
A boy or a girl?

49
00:04:04,639 --> 00:04:07,409
A guy. A male classmate.

50
00:04:07,409 --> 00:04:09,248
Cheers!

51
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:16,720
Come on, eat up.

52
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,745
Ke Ke has grown into
such a handsome young man.

53
00:04:18,745 --> 00:04:20,358
And he's so smart.

54
00:04:20,358 --> 00:04:23,280
He's definitely going to
have a bright future.

55
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:25,840
He just spent a few extra years in school.

56
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:27,520
At least he's not illiterate.

57
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:31,559
In the future, I'll be happy as long as
he doesn't cause me trouble.

58
00:04:31,559 --> 00:04:33,160
Mr. Chen, you're too modest.

59
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,600
If my silly kid

60
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,600
could get into a school
as good as Mingde University,

61
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,764
I'd be over the moon.

62
00:04:38,764 --> 00:04:39,999
Enough talk.

63
00:04:39,999 --> 00:04:41,799
Let's have a drink.

64
00:04:47,679 --> 00:04:49,359
I'm done, everyone.

65
00:04:49,359 --> 00:04:50,840
- I'll head out first.
- Okay.

66
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,176
Hey.

67
00:05:19,999 --> 00:05:21,365
That's so interesting.

68
00:05:21,365 --> 00:05:24,320
- I really loved it.
- That actor is very famous.

69
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:35,640
Okay, see you there!

70
00:05:37,439 --> 00:05:38,679
- Old Yu.
- Yeah?

71
00:05:38,679 --> 00:05:40,520
Aunt Chen wants you to come along too.

72
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,759
Get your coat, let's go.

73
00:05:41,759 --> 00:05:43,971
What's the rush? Alright, alright.

74
00:05:50,721 --> 00:05:53,239
The number you have dialed is not answering.

75
00:05:53,239 --> 00:05:55,640
Please try again later.

76
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,875
Hey.

77
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:24,600
It's school break
and you're still running at school?

78
00:06:25,759 --> 00:06:26,999
Let me guess.

79
00:06:26,999 --> 00:06:29,799
Could it be that
you failed your fitness test last semester,

80
00:06:29,799 --> 00:06:32,639
and you have to retake the 800m
when school starts?

81
00:06:34,199 --> 00:06:36,040
Can't I just be exercising?

82
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:38,599
You big gorilla. Mind your own business.

83
00:06:39,439 --> 00:06:42,999
At your speed,
even an old lady will pass you.

84
00:06:42,999 --> 00:06:45,559
You! Why do you have so much to say?

85
00:06:45,559 --> 00:06:47,679
Just run.

86
00:06:48,879 --> 00:06:51,640
You should be grateful
to have a coach like me.

87
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,640
Seriously.

88
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,439
Right, right.

89
00:06:55,439 --> 00:06:57,880
Go, go! Pick it up!

90
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,880
How was it?

91
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:13,509
- Yes!
- I think you'll pass, right?

92
00:07:13,509 --> 00:07:15,239
Not bad.

93
00:07:18,199 --> 00:07:21,799
Well... thanks.

94
00:07:23,679 --> 00:07:26,920
Look at you, little poodle,
actually saying thank you.

95
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,439
Shut up.

96
00:07:29,439 --> 00:07:31,239
I'm going to find Yu Lei.

97
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,552
[Victoria Italian Restaurant]

98
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,960
Hey. A few days ago, didn't you say

99
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,520
that you'd spend the break
practicing your running?

100
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:47,119
It's only been a few days,

101
00:07:47,119 --> 00:07:49,239
and you're dragging me out to play again.

102
00:07:49,239 --> 00:07:52,080
Work hard, play hard. It's all about balance.

103
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:58,199
Li Ming has been training at school
all winter break.

104
00:07:58,199 --> 00:07:59,880
Why don't you ask him for some tips?

105
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:02,040
They're selling toys over there.
Let's go check it out.

106
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:05,640
- Let's go.
- Come take a look, everything's on sale!

107
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,360
Come see!

108
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,875
Great deals here! Take a look!

109
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:11,319
Look at this.

110
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:13,119
Come see! Take a look!

111
00:08:13,119 --> 00:08:15,080
They're very cheap, miss.

112
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:30,280
- Hit it!
- Go, go, go!

113
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,080
Can you do it?

114
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:36,361
- Quick, quick!
- Chen Ke, go hit those mobs over there.

115
00:08:39,439 --> 00:08:42,080
Sorry about that. Force of habit.

116
00:08:44,319 --> 00:08:45,839
Get him, get him!

117
00:08:45,839 --> 00:08:47,161
Yu Lei! Come save me!

118
00:08:47,161 --> 00:08:50,040
- Quick, I'm out of health!
- Coming, coming!

119
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:53,879
Hurry! Hurry!

120
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,799
Yeah!

121
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:57,479
Not bad!

122
00:08:59,079 --> 00:09:00,439
I'm feeling hot.

123
00:09:00,439 --> 00:09:02,276
I'm going to shower first.

124
00:09:02,276 --> 00:09:04,319
You carry on first.

125
00:09:07,599 --> 00:09:09,399
I haven't had enough fun yet.

126
00:09:22,517 --> 00:09:25,015
[Certificate of Merit, Top 3 Student]

127
00:09:25,015 --> 00:09:27,037
[First Prize for Hosting, Yu Lei]

128
00:09:54,319 --> 00:09:55,319
Yu Lei?

129
00:09:55,319 --> 00:09:57,759
Yu Lei is in the shower.

130
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,760
Me?

131
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:03,760
I'm Yu Lei's little sweetheart.

132
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:06,320
What do you want with him?

133
00:10:06,959 --> 00:10:08,800
Stop it, give it back!

134
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:10,839
Hello? Hi.

135
00:10:10,839 --> 00:10:12,160
Who is this?

136
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:14,479
It's me, Chen Ke.

137
00:10:14,479 --> 00:10:16,520
Chen Ke!

138
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:19,400
Why are you only calling me now?
I missed you so much!

139
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:20,559
Stop it!

140
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:24,439
Yu Lei, since when is Ouyang Han
your "sweetheart"?

141
00:10:24,439 --> 00:10:26,239
Get out of here!

142
00:10:29,199 --> 00:10:31,920
No. Ouyang just came to my place
to play games.

143
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,160
He's just messing with you. Don't mind him.

144
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,160
Why would I mind?

145
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:41,920
Anyway, I just wanted to tell you
that I got a new phone.

146
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,240
Okay, go ahead.

147
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,960
- Write this down.
- Okay.

148
00:10:46,959 --> 00:10:48,879
Okay, I got it.

149
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:52,319
Yeah.

150
00:10:52,319 --> 00:10:53,772
Okay.

151
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,880
Is Ouyang Han still staying at your place?

152
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,479
Ke Ke, it's getting late.

153
00:11:06,479 --> 00:11:08,559
Go to sleep.

154
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:10,792
I know.

155
00:11:10,792 --> 00:11:13,313
My mom is nagging me to sleep again.

156
00:11:13,959 --> 00:11:15,599
My mom just did the same thing.

157
00:11:15,599 --> 00:11:16,959
I thought it was still early,

158
00:11:16,959 --> 00:11:19,479
but I looked at the clock
and it's already 1 AM.

159
00:11:21,079 --> 00:11:24,439
- Wait, no. It's already 1:30 AM.
- What?

160
00:11:24,439 --> 00:11:27,160
My phone is burning up.

161
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:31,559
Tell you what. Let's count to three,
and then we both hang up.

162
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:32,679
Okay.

163
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:33,920
One.

164
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,520
Two.

165
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,054
Three.

166
00:11:39,679 --> 00:11:41,479
Why didn't you hang up?

167
00:11:42,319 --> 00:11:44,120
- You hang up first.
- No, you.

168
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,479
You first.

169
00:11:45,479 --> 00:11:47,120
Fine. I'm hanging up now.

170
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,415
Okay.

171
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,079
2001.

172
00:11:54,079 --> 00:11:55,199
Winter break.

173
00:11:55,199 --> 00:11:57,040
Sunny.

174
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,839
I'm grateful for technology.

175
00:11:58,839 --> 00:12:02,520
Even though we're far apart,
we can still talk every day.

176
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:05,240
It's like we were never separated.

177
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:09,199
Whenever I think about it,
my heart feels like a bird,

178
00:12:09,199 --> 00:12:12,359
singing a melody I've never heard before.

179
00:12:25,559 --> 00:12:26,744
I forgot to tell you,

180
00:12:26,744 --> 00:12:28,920
my mom has seen me glued to my phone lately.

181
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,759
She thinks I'm in love.

182
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,127
Goodnight.

183
00:12:36,599 --> 00:12:38,399
Goodnight.

184
00:13:59,479 --> 00:14:04,360
Late at night, I wake up drenched in sweat.

185
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:06,439
That dream felt so real.

186
00:14:06,439 --> 00:14:09,360
I can still feel the warmth on my lips.

187
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:12,839
It's a strange feeling, but...

188
00:14:12,839 --> 00:14:15,320
deep down, I'm a little happy.

189
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:22,120
Dinner's ready!

190
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:24,199
Come and eat.

191
00:14:24,199 --> 00:14:26,239
Eat more, son.

192
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,839
Put the phone away.

193
00:14:31,839 --> 00:14:33,520
Focus on your meal.

194
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:35,719
Old Chen, what are you doing?

195
00:14:35,719 --> 00:14:38,119
The boy is on his school break.

196
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,240
By the way, there's a dinner tonight.

197
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:45,599
Director Zhao's son is taking
the college entrance exam next year.

198
00:14:45,599 --> 00:14:47,439
He knows you're at Mingde University,

199
00:14:47,439 --> 00:14:49,120
so he specifically asked me
to bring you along

200
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,400
to share some of your experience.

201
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,760
Why is there a dinner every single day?

202
00:14:57,199 --> 00:15:00,719
You're getting more and more disrespectful.

203
00:15:00,719 --> 00:15:03,160
You barely even acknowledge me when I speak.

204
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,960
Give me the phone.

205
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,079
Chen Ke.

206
00:15:08,079 --> 00:15:10,280
What's wrong with you?

207
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,599
Are you trying to rebel?

208
00:15:12,599 --> 00:15:14,199
Alright, alright.

209
00:15:14,199 --> 00:15:15,520
Stop shouting.

210
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:17,720
Can we just eat?

211
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:21,360
I know exactly what you're going to say.

212
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:25,319
I'm disrespectful,
disobedient, embarrassing you,

213
00:15:25,319 --> 00:15:27,559
and I think I'm all grown up now. Right?

214
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:28,880
You...

215
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,520
Lost for words?

216
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:33,079
Are you going to slap me again?

217
00:15:33,079 --> 00:15:35,240
You say I don't listen to you,

218
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:37,387
but every time you come home late
from those dinners,

219
00:15:37,387 --> 00:15:40,240
and Mom tries to talk to you,
do you ever listen to her?

220
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:42,592
When things happen at school
and I come home to tell you,

221
00:15:42,592 --> 00:15:44,240
do you ever listen to me?

222
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:47,079
Ke Ke, that's enough.

223
00:15:47,079 --> 00:15:49,520
You always just
wash your hands of everything.

224
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:52,520
You haven't even been to
a single parent-teacher meeting.

225
00:15:53,439 --> 00:15:56,120
Do you even consider this place a home?

226
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:59,719
To you, I'm just a son you can brag about
to others.

227
00:15:59,719 --> 00:16:02,960
That's my only value to you, isn't it?

228
00:16:04,512 --> 00:16:06,839
Since you can't stand the sight of me,

229
00:16:06,839 --> 00:16:08,880
I'll pack my things
and go back to school right now.

230
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:11,560
- Ke Ke!
- You...

231
00:16:45,199 --> 00:16:46,520
Hello, Professor.

232
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:47,880
This is Chen Ke.

233
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:50,320
Is it possible to return to campus early?

234
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,762
- Hello, son?
- Hi, Mom.

235
00:17:26,762 --> 00:17:28,231
You're already back at school, aren't you?

236
00:17:28,231 --> 00:17:29,840
I'm in my dorm. Don't worry.

237
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:32,819
Honestly, why did you have to
go back a week early?

238
00:17:32,819 --> 00:17:35,560
Mom, since Dad was so unhappy
with me being there,

239
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:38,799
leaving early is exactly
what he wanted, right?

240
00:17:39,519 --> 00:17:41,519
Your father, he's just...

241
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:43,920
Mom, I think my roommate is back.

242
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:47,285
- I have to go. Take care of yourself.
- Okay.

243
00:17:52,679 --> 00:17:54,199
Surprise!

244
00:17:54,199 --> 00:17:55,703
Well? Are you surprised?

245
00:17:55,703 --> 00:17:57,406
Didn't see that coming, did you?

246
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,666
[Comrades: Almost A Love Story]

247
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:20,679
I didn't realize you missed me this much.

248
00:18:20,679 --> 00:18:21,880
I didn't.

249
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,759
I was just bored being home alone.

250
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,120
Really?

251
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:30,560
Was it because I wasn't there
that you were bored?

252
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:32,640
Wow, you really think highly of yourself.

253
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,440
I'm ignoring you.

254
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:37,137
Ta-da!

255
00:18:40,999 --> 00:18:42,719
Ignoring me?

256
00:18:42,719 --> 00:18:45,320
Then I'll just give this to someone else.

257
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,120
Childish.

258
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:52,719
Why are you giving me this?

259
00:18:52,719 --> 00:18:56,160
Do you remember when we watched
that movie together?

260
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:58,160
I said you were crying like a little squirrel,

261
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:00,080
and you said I was like a sly old fox.

262
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:01,960
So, we make a perfect pair.

263
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:09,560
Why did you pick the cute one for yourself,
and give me the...

264
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:13,200
Fine. If you like the fox better,
we can swap.

265
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,120
You already gave it to me.

266
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,920
I'm not swapping.

267
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,840
What?

268
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:29,160
Wong Fei Hung?
(Famous martial artist and folk hero)

269
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,120
Where's my gift?

270
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,959
If you don't have one, just say so.

271
00:19:38,959 --> 00:19:40,960
Why are you hitting me?

272
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:43,920
Come on. I want to show you something.

273
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:46,479
Where? Where are we going?

274
00:19:50,199 --> 00:19:52,320
How do you have the key to the piano room?

275
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:53,320
Don't worry.

276
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,519
After Professor Meng heard me play last time,

277
00:19:55,519 --> 00:20:00,719
he applied for a key for me
so I can come and practice whenever I want.

278
00:20:00,719 --> 00:20:04,439
I didn't realize you'd become
so privileged so quickly.

279
00:20:04,439 --> 00:20:06,239
It's not like that.

280
00:20:15,039 --> 00:20:18,120
Why do you always carry this around?

281
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:20,840
When I was little
and learning from my grandma,

282
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:23,239
she told me to always have it with me.

283
00:20:23,239 --> 00:20:27,199
Every time I play,
I record it so I can listen back later.

284
00:20:27,199 --> 00:20:29,880
It helps me see where I need to improve.

285
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:33,039
So, it's just become a habit over the years.

286
00:20:33,039 --> 00:20:36,239
I bring it whenever I'm going to play piano.

287
00:20:36,239 --> 00:20:40,839
So, you brought me here
just to watch you practice?

288
00:20:41,752 --> 00:20:44,439
You helped me fulfill
my grandma's wish last time.

289
00:20:44,439 --> 00:20:45,999
I didn't know how to thank you.

290
00:20:45,999 --> 00:20:48,600
But now I've thought of something.

291
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,400
What is it?

292
00:21:47,759 --> 00:21:51,839
Sorry, I haven't finished the ending yet.

293
00:21:54,439 --> 00:21:56,959
It's beautiful.

294
00:21:56,959 --> 00:21:58,432
What piece is that?

295
00:21:58,432 --> 00:22:00,439
I've never heard it before.

296
00:22:00,439 --> 00:22:02,039
Is it Bach?

297
00:22:02,039 --> 00:22:03,600
Beethoven?

298
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:05,600
Mozart?

299
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,080
None of them.

300
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:09,840
It's a melody I hummed out during the break.

301
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:12,120
I thought it sounded nice,

302
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:14,160
so I wrote it down.

303
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,880
I told myself that when I got back,

304
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,199
you'd be the first person to hear it.

305
00:22:18,199 --> 00:22:23,319
So, you wrote a song just for us?

306
00:22:25,759 --> 00:22:28,519
And I'm the first person
in the world to hear it.

307
00:22:29,439 --> 00:22:30,920
What do you think?

308
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:33,720
Ke Ke, I love it.

309
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:38,640
Well, if you like it,
I can teach you how to play it.

310
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:41,319
Don't worry, I'm a good teacher.

311
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:43,920
I think I'll pass.

312
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,400
Look at my hands.

313
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,759
They're like bear paws.

314
00:22:47,759 --> 00:22:48,959
I can't play the piano.

315
00:22:48,959 --> 00:22:50,640
Don't say that.

316
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:52,279
Your hands are cute.

317
00:22:52,279 --> 00:22:54,599
They don't look like bear paws at all.

318
00:23:08,025 --> 00:23:10,666
Do I look like a lucky cat then?

319
00:23:16,959 --> 00:23:18,240
How was your break?

320
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:21,345
It was good.
I haven't exercised properly all break.

321
00:23:21,345 --> 00:23:24,560
I didn't have much going on,
so I came back early.

322
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,360
What's up?

323
00:23:28,439 --> 00:23:30,460
Ouyang?

324
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:32,640
Yu Lei! I was just looking for you.

325
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:33,679
You...

326
00:23:33,679 --> 00:23:35,439
What? What are you looking at?

327
00:23:35,439 --> 00:23:37,929
What's with the hair?

328
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:41,539
It's my new look. What do you think?
Pretty good, right?

329
00:23:41,539 --> 00:23:43,385
It took me forever.

330
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:49,160
Chen Ke, what do you think?

331
00:23:51,519 --> 00:23:55,960
Oh, look, it's the copycat.

332
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:59,079
Who are you calling a copycat?

333
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:02,640
They say wearing the same outfit isn't scary.

334
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:05,400
It's only awkward for the ugly one.

335
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,759
You!

336
00:24:06,759 --> 00:24:08,559
Let me play with that.

337
00:24:10,959 --> 00:24:12,759
Just you wait.

338
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:17,439
Yu Lei, isn't the Student Union
recruiting new members?

339
00:24:17,439 --> 00:24:18,719
Let's go together.

340
00:24:18,719 --> 00:24:20,120
Sure.

341
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:22,640
Ke Ke, come with us.

342
00:24:23,439 --> 00:24:25,279
You guys go ahead.

343
00:24:25,279 --> 00:24:26,439
- But...
- Let's go.

344
00:24:26,439 --> 00:24:28,799
They'll run out of forms if we're late.

345
00:24:32,238 --> 00:24:33,799
Thank you.

346
00:24:38,694 --> 00:24:40,494
Next.

347
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,081
Hello, everyone. My name is Yu Lei.

348
00:24:48,081 --> 00:24:50,360
I'm a freshman in the Law School.

349
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:53,199
I'm applying to join the Student Union's
Organizing Department.

350
00:24:53,199 --> 00:24:57,360
Yu Lei, tell us,
why do you want to join the Student Union?

351
00:24:57,360 --> 00:24:58,800
And what are your strengths?

352
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,080
I want to join the Student Union

353
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:03,439
because I want to make a real difference
and serve my fellow students.

354
00:25:03,439 --> 00:25:06,439
I also want to challenge myself
and improve my skills.

355
00:25:06,439 --> 00:25:10,959
As for my strengths,
I'm outgoing and energetic,

356
00:25:10,959 --> 00:25:12,600
and I'm a good communicator.

357
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,039
Back in high school,

358
00:25:14,039 --> 00:25:16,719
I was class president
and Student Union president.

359
00:25:16,719 --> 00:25:20,039
And last year, I hosted the school's
freshman orientation gala.

360
00:25:20,039 --> 00:25:22,360
I have experience organizing events,

361
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:25,320
so I believe I can quickly adapt
to the pace of the Student Union.

362
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:27,400
If you were asked
to organize a large-scale event,

363
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,240
how would you go about it?

364
00:25:30,782 --> 00:25:34,360
First, I would define
the goals and the budget.

365
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:37,640
Then, I'd put together a team
and delegate tasks.

366
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:40,410
During the planning phase,

367
00:25:40,410 --> 00:25:43,999
I'd hold regular meetings
to make sure everything is on track.

368
00:25:43,999 --> 00:25:46,880
Finally, after the event,
I'd review what happened

369
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:49,880
to prepare for the next one.

370
00:25:52,719 --> 00:25:54,160
Is this you?

371
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,279
Why am I not on here?

372
00:25:55,279 --> 00:25:57,960
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me. Coming through.

373
00:25:58,719 --> 00:26:00,759
I'm in the Arts Department!

374
00:26:00,759 --> 00:26:01,999
That's great.

375
00:26:01,999 --> 00:26:03,640
Yu Lei, you're there!

376
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:06,400
No big deal. Piece of cake.

377
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:08,999
I wish we were both on the list.

378
00:26:08,999 --> 00:26:11,119
Keep looking, maybe you're there.

379
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,160
Found it! I'm right there.

380
00:26:17,999 --> 00:26:19,479
It's okay, there's always next time.

381
00:26:19,479 --> 00:26:21,400
I thought that was me.

382
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,519
Don't worry, look again.

383
00:26:25,999 --> 00:26:28,799
It's fine. There's always next year.

384
00:26:30,389 --> 00:26:33,080
Let's go eat to celebrate.

385
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:34,920
- Okay. Alright. Let's go.
- Let's go.

386
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,880
- I don't think she's even as good as me.
- Exactly.

387
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,520
- He got in too.
- Oh, wait.

388
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:41,480
- What?
- I'll text Chen Ke and ask him to join us.

389
00:26:46,679 --> 00:26:49,360
Actually, I just remembered
I have something to do.

390
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:50,600
I'll head out first.

391
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:53,039
You guys go ahead and eat.

392
00:26:53,039 --> 00:26:55,600
Okay. See you later then.

393
00:27:10,999 --> 00:27:12,239
What are you doing?

394
00:27:12,239 --> 00:27:13,439
Why aren't you eating?

395
00:27:13,439 --> 00:27:15,239
I'm on a diet.

396
00:27:15,239 --> 00:27:17,560
Please. Give me a break.

397
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:20,160
You, on a diet?

398
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:21,960
None of your business.

399
00:27:23,239 --> 00:27:27,439
Look, I know it's about the Student Union.

400
00:27:27,439 --> 00:27:29,066
It's not a big deal.

401
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:32,800
Here. Just eat. And drink.

402
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:36,200
You'll feel better once you've had something.

403
00:27:38,199 --> 00:27:39,840
I don't want your charity.

404
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:41,640
No thanks.

405
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,439
Well, I'm leaving it here.

406
00:27:44,439 --> 00:27:45,519
Eat it or leave it.

407
00:27:45,519 --> 00:27:47,080
I have class. I'm off.

408
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:48,363
Wait.

409
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,479
Now what?

410
00:27:50,479 --> 00:27:52,279
Well...

411
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:54,439
I passed my 800m retake.

412
00:27:54,439 --> 00:27:56,999
I never got to say thank you.

413
00:27:56,999 --> 00:27:59,560
It was nothing. Don't worry about it.

414
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:01,360
See ya.

415
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:05,640
The food looks good today.

416
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:07,004
Yeah.

417
00:28:08,439 --> 00:28:10,160
Well, if it isn't our campus celebrity.

418
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:12,920
I'm surprised you're eating
with us commoners.

419
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:15,319
D-Don't be like that.

420
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:19,680
Come, sit down.

421
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:25,959
Here. Have a chicken leg.

422
00:28:25,959 --> 00:28:27,920
I'm fine.

423
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:35,039
He Jin, are you looking for a seat?

424
00:28:35,039 --> 00:28:36,239
Sit here.

425
00:28:36,239 --> 00:28:38,439
I think I'll pass.

426
00:28:38,439 --> 00:28:40,746
A regular guy like me

427
00:28:40,746 --> 00:28:44,120
isn't worthy of sitting with
the future Student Union president.

428
00:28:45,239 --> 00:28:47,519
What's that supposed to mean?

429
00:28:47,519 --> 00:28:51,160
Everyone knows the current president,
Zhang Han, is your cousin.

430
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:53,560
It helps to have friends in high places.

431
00:28:57,160 --> 00:28:59,959
There's also a saying:
"Promote talent regardless of kinship."

432
00:28:59,959 --> 00:29:02,920
Yu Lei has good grades, he's popular,
and he's capable.

433
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:04,920
If you're not happy,
you should have applied yourself.

434
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:06,600
It's a fair competition.

435
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,640
Don't be so passive-aggressive
just because you didn't make it.

436
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:11,080
It just makes you look like a sore loser.

437
00:29:15,519 --> 00:29:16,560
It's okay.

438
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:20,039
He Jin applied too, but he didn't get in.

439
00:29:20,039 --> 00:29:22,680
He's just jealous. Don't let it get to you.

440
00:29:24,479 --> 00:29:28,039
You want to leave the Student Union? Why?

441
00:29:28,039 --> 00:29:30,080
No reason.

442
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:34,279
I just suddenly feel like the responsibility
is bigger than I thought.

443
00:29:34,279 --> 00:29:36,120
I don't think I'm cut out for it.

444
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,840
Then why did you apply?

445
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:39,640
I...

446
00:29:42,559 --> 00:29:44,119
Is it because of me?

447
00:29:44,119 --> 00:29:45,559
Because people are talking?

448
00:29:45,559 --> 00:29:47,000
Are they gossiping about you?

449
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,559
No.

450
00:29:48,559 --> 00:29:50,640
I just don't want to do it anymore.

451
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:52,721
Yu Lei, if you're doing this

452
00:29:52,721 --> 00:29:55,240
because you're afraid of
what people will say about us,

453
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:57,519
then let me be clear.

454
00:29:57,519 --> 00:30:01,880
Every single candidate was discussed
and reviewed by the entire committee.

455
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:04,839
The faculty advisors
also oversaw the process.

456
00:30:04,839 --> 00:30:08,119
Even though I'm the president,
I only have one vote.

457
00:30:08,119 --> 00:30:09,960
Everyone believes in you.

458
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:12,519
There was no favoritism.

459
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:15,839
But I don't have the confidence
to do a good job now.

460
00:30:17,319 --> 00:30:19,039
No confidence?

461
00:30:19,039 --> 00:30:22,200
I never thought
I'd hear those words from you.

462
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:25,880
Haven't you always been the one
charging ahead with a smile?

463
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:28,079
There are billions of people in this world,

464
00:30:28,079 --> 00:30:29,720
and everyone has their own opinion.

465
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:32,279
We can't control what they say.

466
00:30:32,279 --> 00:30:34,400
We can only control what we do.

467
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:37,951
As long as we have a clear conscience
and do our jobs well,

468
00:30:37,951 --> 00:30:40,720
what others say shouldn't matter.

469
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:48,880
Lei Lei, the Student Union
is a serious organization.

470
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:52,759
It's not a place where you can just
quit on a whim.

471
00:30:52,759 --> 00:30:57,200
So today, I'm not accepting your resignation.

472
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:58,301
But I...

473
00:30:58,301 --> 00:31:01,480
I can see that you're upset.

474
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:05,079
And you shouldn't make any big decisions
when you're like this.

475
00:31:05,079 --> 00:31:07,319
Go back and think about it.

476
00:31:07,319 --> 00:31:08,839
I'll come find you the day after tomorrow.

477
00:31:08,839 --> 00:31:11,359
If you still feel the same way then,

478
00:31:11,359 --> 00:31:13,280
I'll respect your decision.

479
00:31:29,839 --> 00:31:33,200
I've always looked up to my cousin.

480
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:36,160
I remember once, I failed a math test,

481
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:38,760
and locked myself in my room to cry.

482
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:42,960
When she found out,
she didn't say a word,

483
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:45,039
she just rushed over to my house.

484
00:31:45,039 --> 00:31:46,400
That night,

485
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:49,519
she stayed with me
until I understood every single problem.

486
00:31:49,519 --> 00:31:54,000
She told me that failure isn't scary.

487
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:58,440
What matters is what you learn from it.

488
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:00,880
She really cares about you.

489
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:01,920
She does.

490
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,960
And another time,
I was in a city-wide speech competition.

491
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:07,119
I was so nervous,

492
00:32:07,119 --> 00:32:10,839
so she took time off school
to come and cheer for me.

493
00:32:10,839 --> 00:32:15,480
She even taught me how to
calm my nerves before going on stage.

494
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:18,240
I won first place that time,

495
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:20,799
all thanks to her encouragement.

496
00:32:20,799 --> 00:32:23,839
She's smart, capable,

497
00:32:23,839 --> 00:32:26,781
and she excels at everything she does.

498
00:32:26,781 --> 00:32:28,480
She's always been my idol.

499
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,839
I want to be just like her.

500
00:32:30,839 --> 00:32:32,519
But now...

501
00:32:32,519 --> 00:32:35,519
But you're already doing so well.

502
00:32:35,519 --> 00:32:39,400
I know my cousin is a fair person.

503
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:40,920
She's honest and upright.

504
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:44,241
She would never show favoritism
just because I'm her relative.

505
00:32:45,079 --> 00:32:48,079
I don't care what people say about me.

506
00:32:48,079 --> 00:32:49,880
I can take it.

507
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:53,559
But because of this, people might think...

508
00:32:54,839 --> 00:32:56,880
she's being unfair.

509
00:32:56,880 --> 00:32:59,640
I didn't think it through at the time.

510
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:03,399
I think it's better if I just quit.

511
00:33:08,441 --> 00:33:10,425
Yu Lei, when you take an exam,

512
00:33:10,425 --> 00:33:13,559
is it you or your cousin taking it?

513
00:33:13,559 --> 00:33:15,160
Me, of course.

514
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,160
Why?

515
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:18,440
And the orientation gala. Was it you hosting,

516
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:20,359
or was it her?

517
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:23,519
Since you're the one doing all these things,

518
00:33:23,519 --> 00:33:25,920
it proves your ability.

519
00:33:25,920 --> 00:33:28,039
Everyone can see that.

520
00:33:28,039 --> 00:33:29,640
Mingde University is a top school.

521
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:31,160
It's full of brilliant people.

522
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:33,119
They wouldn't let someone incompetent

523
00:33:33,119 --> 00:33:35,359
join the Student Union
just because of connections.

524
00:33:35,359 --> 00:33:38,559
Why can't you just trust
everyone's judgment?

525
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:44,680
But... I...

526
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:47,920
They say love is always feeling like
you haven't done enough.

527
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:50,920
I think you're only this conflicted

528
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:54,039
because you care so much about her.

529
00:33:54,039 --> 00:33:56,240
You're afraid people will misunderstand her.

530
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:58,079
But she trusts you.

531
00:33:58,079 --> 00:34:01,960
She's not afraid of the gossip,
so why are you?

532
00:34:05,279 --> 00:34:07,799
A few jealous people
talking behind your back

533
00:34:07,799 --> 00:34:09,320
won't change anything.

534
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:13,640
It only shows their own insecurity
and jealousy.

535
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,559
Alright.

536
00:34:17,559 --> 00:34:19,079
Come practice baseball with me.

537
00:34:19,079 --> 00:34:22,080
Maybe you'll feel better after some exercise.

538
00:34:40,559 --> 00:34:43,840
Ke Ke, thank you.

539
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,440
I think I've got it now.

540
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:46,480
Don't mention it.

541
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,680
I just want you to be happy.

542
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:57,119
I used to hear the story of
Hou Yi shooting the suns.

543
00:34:57,119 --> 00:35:01,480
For some reason,
I always thought it was a very sad story.

544
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:05,000
The sun had nine brothers, but in the end,

545
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:07,160
it was the only one left.

546
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:10,280
How lonely that must be.

547
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:16,680
The newspapers say only children
are like little suns.

548
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:19,480
But I'd rather be a star.

549
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:22,920
That way, I'd have so many companions,

550
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:24,760
and I'd never be lonely.

551
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:29,320
So, in your heart,
am I one of those stars too?

552
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,827
Yes,

553
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,959
but also no.

554
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:38,679
I think we're like binary stars.

555
00:35:38,679 --> 00:35:42,079
Orbiting each other, bound together.

556
00:35:42,079 --> 00:35:44,280
Pulled by gravity,

557
00:35:45,679 --> 00:35:47,640
we can never be apart.

558
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:55,399
Ke Ke, it's good to have you here.

559
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:07,480
A new school year has begun.

560
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:12,239
We've just finished recruiting for the clubs
and the Student Union.

561
00:36:12,239 --> 00:36:14,360
Every department has new members.

562
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:16,199
Please look out for one another.

563
00:36:16,199 --> 00:36:18,599
If you have any questions or need any help,

564
00:36:18,599 --> 00:36:20,519
you can always come to me.

565
00:36:21,199 --> 00:36:23,239
That's all for today's meeting.

566
00:36:23,239 --> 00:36:25,440
- Alright.
- Okay, let's go.

567
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,440
Let's go get something to eat.

568
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,000
I'm heading out.

569
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:33,000
Let's go over those notes later.

570
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,280
Sure.

571
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:36,679
- Sis.
- Lei Lei.

572
00:36:36,679 --> 00:36:39,119
How's everything in
the Organizing Department?

573
00:36:39,119 --> 00:36:40,320
It's going well.

574
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,320
That's good.

575
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:44,440
The head of the department
was just praising you the other day.

576
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:47,440
He said you're the most proactive
of all the new members.

577
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:48,840
Of course!

578
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,760
I can't let the president down, can I?

579
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:53,920
There you go again.

580
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:57,039
Who was it that was crying about quitting?

581
00:36:57,039 --> 00:36:59,720
You're like a completely
different person now.

582
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:03,920
Actually, it's all thanks to Chen Ke.

583
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:06,880
I was just being stubborn,

584
00:37:06,880 --> 00:37:08,880
and he helped me see things clearly.

585
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:11,840
Well, Chen Ke seems to
understand you pretty well.

586
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,320
He does.

587
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:16,320
We're like soulmates.

588
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:18,702
A rare connection.

589
00:37:18,702 --> 00:37:22,920
Lei Lei, what do you think of Chen Ke?

590
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:25,000
He's great.

591
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,999
Why do you ask?

592
00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:29,960
No reason. Just curious.

593
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,639
Just getting to know him.

594
00:37:31,639 --> 00:37:33,119
It's been a while since we've eaten together.

595
00:37:33,119 --> 00:37:35,880
What do you want? My treat.

596
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,035
I want stir-fry!

597
00:37:37,035 --> 00:37:38,835
Alright.

598
00:37:44,599 --> 00:37:47,000
Yu Lei, Chen Ke only showed you a few times,

599
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:48,639
and you've already got the hang of it.

600
00:37:48,639 --> 00:37:51,480
I had a good teacher.

601
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,807
Yu Lei.

602
00:37:53,752 --> 00:37:57,000
About that thing I asked you to look into...

603
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,320
- The competition in Tianjin?
- Yeah.

604
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:01,699
Don't worry. I've already signed you guys up.

605
00:38:01,699 --> 00:38:04,189
See? Here's the invitation.

606
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:12,039
Thank you so much, Yu Lei!

607
00:38:12,039 --> 00:38:13,239
No problem.

608
00:38:13,239 --> 00:38:16,400
Since I'm in the Student Union,
I have to serve the people, right?

609
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:19,119
Guys! We're going to the competition!

610
00:38:19,119 --> 00:38:21,039
Yu Lei got us the invitation!

611
00:38:21,039 --> 00:38:23,119
- No way!
- Really?

612
00:38:23,119 --> 00:38:25,320
- Let me see!
- What do you think, Ke Ke?

613
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:28,200
Surprised? Didn't see that coming, did you?

614
00:38:29,199 --> 00:38:34,839
Guys, don't we owe Yu Lei a proper thank you?

615
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:44,200
Yu Lei!

616
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:48,719
Ke Ke.

617
00:38:48,719 --> 00:38:50,280
What's wrong?

618
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:52,079
Aren't you happy about the competition?

619
00:38:52,079 --> 00:38:53,199
I am.

620
00:38:53,199 --> 00:38:54,599
It's just...

621
00:38:54,599 --> 00:38:58,480
Why didn't you tell me about this sooner?

622
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:00,140
When the club president came to me,

623
00:39:00,140 --> 00:39:03,562
I thought if I could get you all in,

624
00:39:03,562 --> 00:39:07,559
you and everyone else would be so happy.

625
00:39:07,559 --> 00:39:10,280
So I asked him to keep it a secret.

626
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,960
I wanted it to be a surprise.

627
00:39:11,960 --> 00:39:13,559
What's wrong?

628
00:39:13,559 --> 00:39:15,639
Did I do something wrong?

629
00:39:15,639 --> 00:39:18,479
No. I'm happy.

630
00:39:21,719 --> 00:39:23,000
That's weird.

631
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:25,200
How did it run out so fast?

632
00:39:26,215 --> 00:39:27,679
Maybe someone's taking it.

633
00:39:27,679 --> 00:39:29,280
I heard that happens in other dorms.

634
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:32,560
They steal supplements, even toilet paper.

635
00:39:33,870 --> 00:39:36,079
Don't look at me. I didn't take it.

636
00:39:36,079 --> 00:39:37,239
Stop guessing.

637
00:39:37,239 --> 00:39:39,440
Maybe I just forgot to put the cap back on.

638
00:39:39,440 --> 00:39:42,919
Anyway, just keep an eye on your stuff.

639
00:39:51,519 --> 00:39:54,119
He Jin, can't you soak your feet earlier?

640
00:39:54,119 --> 00:39:55,880
It's so late.

641
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:57,480
It's my routine.

642
00:39:57,480 --> 00:40:00,400
But you can't study while you're doing it.

643
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,480
You're being so loud.

644
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,920
We're trying to sleep.

645
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:04,239
Yeah, He Jin.

646
00:40:04,239 --> 00:40:06,639
I don't need this extra time
after lights out.

647
00:40:06,639 --> 00:40:08,000
Forget it. It's late.

648
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,159
Let's just get some rest.

649
00:40:09,159 --> 00:40:11,239
We have an early class tomorrow.

650
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:18,360
The competition is getting closer.

651
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:19,960
I'm actually starting to feel nervous.

652
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,639
Don't be.

653
00:40:21,639 --> 00:40:23,400
The most important thing is to have fun.

654
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,639
Oh, right. It'll be your birthday then.

655
00:40:25,639 --> 00:40:27,639
We should celebrate together.

656
00:40:27,639 --> 00:40:29,800
Okay. I'm looking forward to it.

657
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:30,800
It's late.

658
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:32,600
I'm going to sleep.

659
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:42,840
Early summer, 2001.

660
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,440
Always sunny.

661
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:48,119
I should be happy that Yu Lei is so popular,

662
00:40:48,119 --> 00:40:49,880
but I'm not.

663
00:40:49,880 --> 00:40:53,599
I always imagined my moments of glory
would be shared only with him.

664
00:40:53,599 --> 00:40:55,680
Why is that?

665
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,109
Who is it?

666
00:41:05,109 --> 00:41:07,320
Are they crazy?

667
00:41:07,320 --> 00:41:09,800
Who calls this late at night?

668
00:41:14,065 --> 00:41:15,865
Hello?

669
00:41:19,639 --> 00:41:21,999
Okay. I'm coming.

670
00:41:24,119 --> 00:41:26,440
What's wrong? What happened?

671
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:29,520
Something happened.
Chen Ke got burned by boiling water.

672
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,097
What?

673
00:41:31,097 --> 00:41:32,239
[Next Episode]
Chen Ke, Chen Ke.

674
00:41:32,239 --> 00:41:34,199
All you care about is Chen Ke.

675
00:41:34,199 --> 00:41:37,120
Can't you just look at me for once?

676
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:40,761
Let me tell you, Ouyang Han,
I can see you as a friend,

677
00:41:40,761 --> 00:41:44,081
or even a brother, but never as a lover.

678
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:52,119
If I'm the best Ouyang Han I can be,

679
00:41:52,119 --> 00:41:53,559
will someone love me then?

680
00:41:53,559 --> 00:41:55,439
Of course they will.

681
00:41:57,528 --> 00:41:59,563
Believe it or not, I'll take care of you.

